Farmers say a transformer had a short circuit leading to 16 farms being affected. JOHANNESBURG Sheep farmers in the Northern Cape have been left stranded after about 50,000 hectares of grazing land was burnt in a veld fire in Calvinia.Farmers say a transformer had a short circuit leading to 16 farms being affected.So far they have received donations from farmers in Mpumalanga's Middleburg area and Upington but say it is not enough.Sheep farmer Willem Pheron says most farmers in the area still do not have a plan. There are about 6,000 sheep without food in the area and we don t have a plan at this stage. The Northern Cape Department of Agriculture is still investigating the matter.